title: John Kasich
added: Kasich's tenure as governor was notable for his support for Medicaid expansion under the Affordable Care Act, his work combating the opioid addiction crisis, his attempt (later reversed by Ohio voters in a 2011 referendum) to curtail collective bargaining for public sector employees, his local government funding cuts, his passage of several anti-abortion laws, his veto of a fetal heartbeat law, his tax cuts, and his evolving position on gun control.<ref>https://www.daytondailynews.com/news/kasich-leaves-mark-with-medicaid-tax-cuts-loses-support-conservatives/</ref>
